Stadium 1 Prime Cup

The Prime Cup is a challenge cup in Pokémon Stadium 1, with no species or level restrictions. The cup features four divisions, named for each of the four Poké Ball types in Red, Green, Blue, and Yellow, and two difficulty modes, Round 1 and Round 2.

The player can choose to use either a team selected from rental Pokémon, a team consisting of Pokémon from a connected Game Boy game, or a mix of both.

If the player beats Round 2 of the Master Ball division with a team consisting entirely of Pokémon from a connected Game Boy game, and the player has a Pikachu that they select to use in the last battle of the division, the player will be able to teach the Pikachu Surf after finishing the division.

The rules in this cup are as follows:

  • The player will select three of their six Pokémon to battle with.
  • If one Pokémon on the opposing team is asleep, any moves that can put a second opposing Pokémon to sleep will fail to do so. The player can still inflict a second sleep status on their own party using Rest.
  • If one Pokémon on the opposing team is frozen, any moves that can freeze a second opposing Pokémon will fail to do so.
  • If the player and the opponent both have only one Pokémon left, and one Pokémon uses Selfdestruct or Explosion to knock out both Pokémon, the player who used Selfdestruct or Explosion will lose the match.
  • Two Pokémon of the same species cannot be entered.

Completing this cup or Poké Cup fully on Round 1 will give the player access to to the Doduo Game Boy. Completing both this cup and Poké Cup fully on Round 1 will give the player access to Dodrio Game Boy. In the Japanese version, Nintendo Cup '99 must be completed instead of Poké Cup. The Doduo Game Boy allows a Game Boy game played through Stadium 1 to run at twice the speed, and the Dodrio Game Boy allows it to run at three times the speed.
